    <question>
        <prompt>What was Marcus Garvey's main contribution to the African American community?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Creating the NAACP</option>
            <option letter="b">Promoting Black pride and self-reliance</option>
            <option letter="c">Integrating public schools</option>
            <option letter="d">Leading the Civil Rights Movement</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Marcus Garvey founded the Universal Negro Improvement Association (UNIA) and promoted Black pride, self-reliance, and economic independence through his "Back to Africa" movement and Black-owned businesses.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What was the primary cause of the Red Scare of 1919-1920?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Fear of Native American uprisings</option>
            <option letter="b">Fear of communist revolution in America</option>
            <option letter="c">Fear of Spanish Flu</option>
            <option letter="d">Fear of German invasion</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Red Scare was driven by fear of communist revolution in America following the Russian Revolution, leading to widespread paranoia, deportations, and violations of civil liberties.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What was the main result of the Treaty of Versailles for America?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">America joined the League of Nations</option>
            <option letter="b">America gained new territories</option>
            <option letter="c">The Senate rejected the treaty</option>
            <option letter="d">America received war reparations</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>The U.S. Senate rejected the Treaty of Versailles, largely due to opposition to joining the League of Nations, leading America to make separate peace with Germany.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What was the significance of the 18th Amendment?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It gave women the right to vote</option>
            <option letter="b">It prohibited alcohol nationwide</option>
            <option letter="c">It abolished slavery</option>
            <option letter="d">It created the income tax</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The 18th Amendment, ratified in 1919, prohibited the manufacture, sale, and transportation of alcohol nationwide, leading to the Prohibition era and rise of organized crime.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>How did World War I affect women's roles in American society?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Women lost their jobs after the war</option>
            <option letter="b">Women gained new work opportunities</option>
            <option letter="c">Women were banned from working</option>
            <option letter="d">Women's roles stayed exactly the same</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>World War I created new opportunities for women in the workforce as they took over jobs previously held by men who were fighting, contributing to the eventual passage of women's suffrage.</explanation>
    </question>
